  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package contains a targeted sufficiency-confusion weakener: the decision rationale treats the presence of the relative hemolysis index (RH < 1) acceptance criterion as a sufficient condition for overall patient safety, without addressing model form uncertainty, boundary condition fidelity, or the broader clinical hemolysis risk chain.",
